Class EarthServerGenericClient.AbstractSceneModel

Abstract base class for scene models.
Defined in: SceneModules.js.

Method Detail
{boolean} checkReceivedData(data)
Validates the received data from the server request. Checks if a texture and a heightmap are available at the moment.
Parameters:
data
- Received data from the server request.
Returns:
{boolean} - TRUE if OK, FALSE if some data is missing
createPlaceHolder()
This creates a placeholder Element for the model. It consists of an simple quad. Models that use this placeholder should remove it of course.
{Element} createTransform(xRes, yRes, zRes, minvalue)
Creates the transform for the scene model to fit into the fishtank/cube. This is done automatically by the scene model.
Parameters:
xRes
Size of the received data on the x-axis (e.g. the requested DEM )
yRes
Size of the received data on the y-axis
zRes
Size of the received data on the z-axis
minvalue
Minimum Value along the y-axis (e.g. minimum value in a DEM, so the model starts at it's wished location)
Returns:
{Element}
removePlaceHolder()
Removes the PlaceHolder created in createPlaceHolder(). If already deleted nothing happens.
reportProgress()
Modules report their loading progress to this function which leads the information to the main scene.
setAreaOfInterest(minx, miny, maxx, maxy)
Sets the area of interest for the model (Lower Corner, Upper Corner).
Parameters:
minx
Minimum of lower latitude
miny
Minimum of lower longitude
maxx
Maximum of upper latitude
maxy
Maximum of upper longitude
setDefaults()
Sets the default values. This is done automatically by the scene model.
setImageFormat(imageFormat)
Sets the image format for the server request.
Parameters:
imageFormat
Default format is "png".
setName(modelName)
Sets the name of the scene model. The name is useful for the demo because it appears in the category "Modules".
Parameters:
modelName
Sets the name of model.
setOffset(xOffset, yOffset, zOffset)
Sets the position of the scene model within the fishtank/cube. The function accepts values in the range of 0 and 1 for each parameter.
Parameters:
xOffset
Offset on the x-axis (width).
yOffset
Offset on the y-axis (height).
zOffset
Offset on the z-axis (depth).
setResolution(xRes, zRes)
Sets the resolution of the scene model (if possible).
Parameters:
xRes
Resolution on the x-axis/Latitude
zRes
Resolution on the z-axis/Longitude
setScale(xScale, yScale, zScale)
Sets the size of the scene model compared to the fishtank/cube. The function accepts values in the range of 0 and 1 for each parameter.
Parameters:
xScale
Size of the model on the x-axis (width).
yScale
Size of the model on the y-axis (height).
zScale
Size of the model on the x-axis (width).
setTransparency(transparency)
Sets the initial transparency of the scene model. The function accepts a parameter value in the range of 0 (fully opaque) and 1(fully transparent).
Parameters:
transparency
Value of visibility.
updateTransparency(transparency)
Updates the transparency during runtime of the scene model. The function accepts a value in the range of 0 (fully opaque) and 1(fully transparent).
Parameters:
transparency
